<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>John W. Davis's 1924 presidential campaign was significant because it:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Won the election</option>
            <option letter="b">Revealed deep divisions in the Democratic Party</option>
            <option letter="c">United progressive and conservative Democrats</option>
            <option letter="d">Established a third party</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>John W. Davis's 1924 presidential campaign revealed deep divisions within the Democratic Party. His nomination came only after a bitter convention fight requiring 103 ballots, reflecting the party's split between urban progressives and rural conservatives. As a compromise candidate satisfying neither faction, Davis's campaign struggled against incumbent Calvin Coolidge, resulting in a decisive Republican victory.</explanation>
    </question>
